5:
A caravan... We should probably
avoid getting seen by them, yeah?
8:
Yep. That'd just cause a hassle and
a half. Let's find another route past
here.
13:
Well... So much for that! Let's help
them out, Nimbus!
22:
No touching the merchandise! It
lowers the value, and we can't have
that. This stuff is mighty important
to me!
27:
Looks like you didn't need much help
after all.
31:
No, no. On the contrary—you've
spared me a great deal of effort!
34:
The name's Tahweel. I'm the leader
of this here caravan. As a token of
my gratitude, I'll give you a stellar
bargain on one of my—
37:
Now hold on a minute there. Aren't
you... the Hellcat of the Dunes? You
used to stay with Rolan! Fancy
meeting you here, of all places!
41: Do you know this guy, Nimbus?
45:
He looks familiar. Might have been
one of the peddlers that always
came by Rolan's place.
50:
Are you traveling this land? I'm on
my way to this town here.
54:
No doubt it's fate that's brought us
together in such a place! Would you
mind accompanying me?
57:
I will, of course, compensate you for
your time. In return, I would like a
chance to speak to the Hellcat of
the Dunes himself. Surely I can ask
that much?
62:
Fine, whatever you want.
But just one thing: call me Nimbus.
65:
Oh, my apologies. I wasn't aware of
your real name.
It's nice to meet you, Nimbus.
69:
Is he for real? What kind of business
can you do in a broke-ass town like
this?
73:
I'm pretty sure we came to the right
place. I wonder what he's planning...
76:
Come one, come all, for bargains
galore! We're running a special
promotion today—eighty percent off
ALL items!
79:
E-excuse me...
Do you happen to have any food?
Meat, perhaps?
81:
Various circumstances prevent me
from directly selling certain items...
But if you buy something else,
maybe I could stick it on for free.
84:
R-really? In that case, how about
this?
86:
I can offer you this rug. How much
do you think it'd be worth?
89:
My, my. This is quite the exquisite
fabric. Let me think...
Okay! I'll give you double market
price for it.
92:
D-double?! Truly?!
Thank you so much...
96:
Hey. Are you, uh... trying to go
bankrupt or something?
100:
Good commerce is all about picking
the right place and people to sell to.
That's the secret to keeping the
peace.
104:
Ah, that's right. This next town is a
doozy, tons of goods to sell. I'll be
having you help me out.
107:
Alcohol, procured by... less than
legal means. Anti-government
sentiment is strong in the area, so
this helps them blow off steam.
111:
Is... that a good idea? Encouraging
them to drink to relieve stress?
114:
It's not the most elegant solution, no.
But in this cruel world, people need
a bit of sympathy... and the bottom
of the bottle offers plenty.
116:
But don't misunderstand. I'm not
running a charity here. When there's
an opportunity to make money, I
take it.
122:
Keeping watch drains the stomach,
doesn't it? Here, I brought you dinner.
126:
Oh. Thanks, I guess.
Sorry, uh, did you need something?
130:
Need? No, not really. I just wanted to
talk with you, alone, is all.
135: ...You lost someone very dear to you.
138:
I consulted Rolan many times on
business matters. I... would like to
think he and I were friends of sorts.
140:
I still remember all the stories he
told me about the stars, you know.
143:
Once, I even asked him if he would
let me have you—to join my
caravan. He said no, of course.
147:
Heh. I wouldn't have wanted to work
for anyone crazy enough to hire the
Hellcat of the Dunes anyway.
150:
We made a promise. That we'd do
our best to preserve the peace in
the kingdom in our own ways.
152:
I thought that... if I had you on my
side, I could do that better.
156:
Peace? How exactly did you think 
I was gonna help with that? 
You know what this world is like.
160:
You saw it today, didn't you? Trade
helps people, especially the starving
ones. When people are fed, the
fighting goes down.
162:
If I want to keep doing that, I need to
grow my caravan... I have to expand
the scale of my operation.
165: I need to find a new trade route.
167:
A brand new one, untread by any
other merchant.
173:
I suppose this is where we go our
separate ways. Parting is such
sweet sorrow, isn't it?
176:
Well, you're always traveling around,
so I'm sure we'll get to see each
other again!
179:
Indeed. If we do meet again, I hope
to hear more about your
travels—with no details spared.
187:
If you really wanna know that bad,
come with us. You've already figured
it out anyway, haven't you?
191:
So you did find it... The place beyond
the stars Rolan always spoke of.
196:
Wait, was meeting us your plan all
along?
199:
Oh no, it most definitely was a
coincidence—one which I am
thankful for.
202:
Here, a contract.
In exchange for accompanying you
on your travels, I offer you the
complete cooperation of my
caravan.
206:
A contract? Wow, you're really
serious about this, huh.
210:
And that, my friends, is what we call
a done deal.
213:
I'm flattered you've taken a liking to
me—I trust I can look forward to your
continued patronage?
217:
Heh. Only if you can prove that
you're not all talk.
